      • fetchReport

        public org.w3c.dom.Document fetchReport()
                                 throws LisaException
        This method will load the report into buffer than be be an XML Document object and return it. If perchance you get this ReportKey from a call to a remote CoordinatorServer, then that CoordinatorServer is access to get the report. If the report has already been loaded, this guy gives you the existing reference to the report. If this report was loaded from a random file, then the document is already loaded...
        Specified by:
        fetchReport in class ReportKey
        Returns:
        XML Document of the report as a byte stream
